{
  "texts": [
    "is the dependent variable of interest (the count of commits) for package i in quarter t. In the model, 𝛼!",
    "is the package-specific fixed effects; 𝛾 \" is the time-period fixed effects; 𝑇𝑟𝑒𝑎𝑡𝑚𝑒𝑛𝑡𝐿𝑎𝑛𝑔!",
    "carries the value of 1 if the package i belongs to the language supported by GitHub Copilot at launch (Python or Rust) and 𝐴𝑓𝑡𝑒𝑟𝐶𝑜𝑝𝑖𝑙𝑜𝑡 \" denotes the time after the launch of GitHub Copilot (t ≥ 0) We cluster the standard errors by package in the TWFE analyses.",
    "The coefficient of interest is 𝛽, which estimates the difference between the treatment and control packages after the launch of Copilot.",
    "To ensure that the treated and control packages have a similar trend before the release of GitHub Copilot, we employ the lead-lag model proposed by Autor (2003)."
